 It's great to be here.

20
00:00:44,460 --> 00:00:48,600
 A new year is a new opportunity.

21
00:00:48,600 --> 00:00:52,640
 Vine Church, Yunlong,

22
00:00:52,640 --> 00:00:57,720
 you are about to enter into a new season.

23
00:00:59,080 --> 00:01:03,340
 It will not look like what you've known before.

24
00:01:03,340 --> 00:01:09,620
 God says, "I will do a new thing."

25
00:01:09,620 --> 00:01:14,180
 As someone who's had a relationship with the Vine Church

26
00:01:14,180 --> 00:01:19,180
 for almost 30 years, I am indeed honored and privileged

27
00:01:19,180 --> 00:01:23,540
 to be asked to say a few words on this special day,

28
00:01:23,540 --> 00:01:25,080
 New Year's Eve.

29
00:01:25,080 --> 00:01:27,780
 And may I just say right up front,

30
00:01:27,780 --> 00:01:29,620
 what a wonderful year it's been.

31
00:01:29,620 --> 00:01:36,500
 From those months, those wonderful months preparing at EIS.

32
00:01:36,500 --> 00:01:38,340
 You'll remember those forever, won't you?

33
00:01:38,340 --> 00:01:39,880
 It's amazing.

34
00:01:39,880 --> 00:01:44,880
 The prayer walks, the social events, the barbecues,

35
00:01:44,880 --> 00:01:50,600
 the Vision Sunday, generous offering.

36
00:01:50,600 --> 00:01:53,940
 We're here today because on one Sunday this year,

37
00:01:55,380 --> 00:01:58,180
 people were moved to give enough money

38
00:01:58,180 --> 00:01:59,940
 to actually finance this church.

39
00:01:59,940 --> 00:02:06,760
 The official launch and this wonderful building.

40
00:02:06,760 --> 00:02:11,860
 Beyond any of our wildest dreams,

41
00:02:11,860 --> 00:02:20,380
 my first words, however, may be misconstrued

42
00:02:20,380 --> 00:02:23,900
 as me being a bit of a killjoy.

43
00:02:23,900 --> 00:02:26,660
 Almost as you say, putting a dampener

44
00:02:26,660 --> 00:02:28,120
 on this joyous occasion.

45
00:02:28,120 --> 00:02:32,100
 But I need to say them nonetheless.

46
00:02:32,100 --> 00:02:35,700
 The church is not a building.

47
00:02:35,700 --> 00:02:39,520
 You're allowed to say amen, by the way.

48
00:02:39,520 --> 00:02:40,580
 Any Pentecostals here?

49
00:02:40,580 --> 00:02:41,420
 Yeah, good.

50
00:02:41,420 --> 00:02:42,660
 Church is not a building.

51
00:02:42,660 --> 00:02:47,040
 The church is not a building.

52
00:02:47,040 --> 00:02:51,020
 The word that Jesus was quoted as using

53
00:02:51,020 --> 00:02:54,220
 that we translate as church, ecclesia,

54
00:02:54,220 --> 00:02:59,820
 has nothing to do with a church building.

55
00:02:59,820 --> 00:03:06,600
 But I think this conversation only goes to illustrate

56
00:03:06,600 --> 00:03:09,380
 the confusion that many of us face

57
00:03:09,380 --> 00:03:12,860
 with church being regarded as a place,

58
00:03:12,860 --> 00:03:17,380
 as a building we go to, rather than a thing we are.

59
00:03:19,180 --> 00:03:21,660
 But in a sense, it doesn't matter

60
00:03:21,660 --> 00:03:24,540
 whether we meet in a beautiful crystal cathedral

61
00:03:24,540 --> 00:03:27,140
 or an old scout hut.

62
00:03:27,140 --> 00:03:33,660
 The church is us, the people of God.

63
00:03:33,660 --> 00:03:40,540
 And I believe that this highly impressive building

64
00:03:40,540 --> 00:03:44,900
 here at Ho Sun Lee is a conduit,

65
00:03:44,900 --> 00:03:49,540
 a conduit for us meeting together to thank God,

66
00:03:49,540 --> 00:03:53,860
 to thank God for his faithfulness and goodness

67
00:03:53,860 --> 00:03:56,220
 at the vine for almost 30 years

68
00:03:56,220 --> 00:04:00,600
 and for this amazing past year here at Yuen Long.

69
00:04:00,600 --> 00:04:05,580
 But equally as important is to seek him

70
00:04:05,580 --> 00:04:10,420
 for his presence in the present

71
00:04:11,820 --> 00:04:14,940
 and to ask his guidance for the future.

72
00:04:14,940 --> 00:04:20,980
 I believe this is one of possibly

73
00:04:20,980 --> 00:04:25,540
 the most significant times in church history.

74
00:04:25,540 --> 00:04:29,780
 Give or take a percentage point,

75
00:04:29,780 --> 00:04:33,900
 around 94% of Hong Kong's population

76
00:04:33,900 --> 00:04:36,900
 are currently not part of any church.

77
00:04:36,900 --> 00:04:39,260
 Does that make you feel good?

78
00:04:39,260 --> 00:04:40,700
 It doesn't make me feel good.

79
00:04:41,700 --> 00:04:45,860
 Many in our city, especially the younger generation,

80
00:04:45,860 --> 00:04:47,180
 have lost hope.

81
00:04:47,180 --> 00:04:52,660
 We're seeing an increase in those suffering

82
00:04:52,660 --> 00:04:54,700
 with mental health issues

83
00:04:54,700 --> 00:04:57,940
 and an alarming rise in teenage suicides.

84
00:04:57,940 --> 00:05:01,740
 And in case you haven't noticed,

85
00:05:01,740 --> 00:05:05,060
 our poor seem to be getting poorer.

86
00:05:05,060 --> 00:05:09,620
 What can we do?

87
00:05:10,620 --> 00:05:14,140
 My friends, mark my words.

88
00:05:14,140 --> 00:05:17,500
 This building is significant,

89
00:05:17,500 --> 00:05:23,580
 but not as an aquarium to keep the fish in,

90
00:05:23,580 --> 00:05:30,100
 but as a launching pad for the lifeboats.

91
00:05:30,100 --> 00:05:31,860
 Can I say that again?

92
00:05:31,860 --> 00:05:36,100
 A launching pad for the lifeboats.

93
00:05:36,100 --> 00:05:38,540
 Down those stairs and out there.

94
00:05:39,540 --> 00:05:42,820
 I see this building as an equipping center,

95
00:05:42,820 --> 00:05:47,500
 equipping the saints to man the lifeboats

96
00:05:47,500 --> 00:05:49,140
 to be sent to the lost,

97
00:05:49,140 --> 00:05:54,820
 the lonely, those who've lost hope.

98
00:05:54,820 --> 00:05:58,460
 And I believe there are many fish

99
00:05:58,460 --> 00:06:00,460
 to be caught right here in Yuen Long.

100
00:06:00,460 --> 00:06:07,220
 I declare today that Yuen Long is a freaking village.

101
00:06:08,220 --> 00:06:09,060
 - Amen.

102
00:06:09,060 --> 00:06:14,460
 - An ocean full of fish ready to be caught.

103
00:06:14,460 --> 00:06:20,940
 As I prayed this week, I saw a picture.

104
00:06:20,940 --> 00:06:23,180
 I saw it in two halves.

105
00:06:23,180 --> 00:06:26,900
 The first half was about today.

106
00:06:26,900 --> 00:06:31,500
 The people of this church were gathered together

107
00:06:31,500 --> 00:06:36,500
 and we were like young eaglets in an eagle's nest.

108
00:06:37,340 --> 00:06:42,340
 Safe together, nestling in the mother's arms.

109
00:06:42,340 --> 00:06:46,820
 They were in close community with each other.

110
00:06:46,820 --> 00:06:50,060
 And I think that describes the Vine Yuen Long very, very well.

111
00:06:50,060 --> 00:06:52,100
 You enjoy wonderful community.

112
00:06:52,100 --> 00:06:58,900
 But in the second scene, the eaglets had grown.

113
00:06:58,900 --> 00:07:05,180
 And I saw squadrons of eagles swarming out from Hong San Lee

114
00:07:06,220 --> 00:07:08,460
 to the people of Yuen Long,

115
00:07:08,460 --> 00:07:11,300
 to the people of Hong Kong and beyond.

116
00:07:11,300 --> 00:07:19,300
 This building is to be that nurture place.

117
00:07:19,300 --> 00:07:25,820
 This building is to be that nurture place

118
00:07:25,820 --> 00:07:28,220
 where, oh yes, you enjoy community

119
00:07:28,220 --> 00:07:30,260
 and please go on enjoying community.

120
00:07:30,260 --> 00:07:35,180
 But where you are also prepared, trained,

121
00:07:35,180 --> 00:07:38,860
 equipped to be sent to where the church of Hong Kong

122
00:07:38,860 --> 00:07:43,860
 really is, in our offices, in our schools

123
00:07:43,860 --> 00:07:48,060
 and the housing estates of our city.

124
00:07:48,060 --> 00:07:54,380
 And in that respect, I wanna share a verse.

125
00:07:54,380 --> 00:07:59,500
 It is the motivating verse for this message.

126
00:07:59,500 --> 00:08:00,380
 It is my prayer.

127
00:08:01,380 --> 00:08:05,420
 It is my dream for this church in 2024.

128
00:08:05,420 --> 00:08:10,740
 And I believe that this verse describes you.

129
00:08:10,740 --> 00:08:15,300
 The people who call Vine Yuen Long their home church.

130
00:08:15,300 --> 00:08:17,580
 It's Psalm 1,3.

131
00:08:17,580 --> 00:08:23,140
 That person, Tim,

132
00:08:23,140 --> 00:08:28,660
 that person, Darius,

133
00:08:30,740 --> 00:08:35,700
 is like a tree planted by streams of water

134
00:08:35,700 --> 00:08:39,220
 which yields its fruit in season

135
00:08:39,220 --> 00:08:42,860
 and whose leaf does not wither,

136
00:08:42,860 --> 00:08:47,580
 whatever they do, prospers.

137
00:08:47,580 --> 00:08:51,780
 Now, read my lips for a moment.

138
00:08:51,780 --> 00:08:57,900
 There is no room in this church for spectators.

139
00:08:59,820 --> 00:09:02,460
 Or to be on any church, to be honest.

140
00:09:02,460 --> 00:09:07,260
 Christianity is not a spectator sport.

141
00:09:07,260 --> 00:09:13,060
 The Psalmist has already told us this in verse one.

142
00:09:13,060 --> 00:09:16,260
 Blessed is the one who does not walk in the step

143
00:09:16,260 --> 00:09:19,420
 with the wicked or stand in the way that sinners take

144
00:09:19,420 --> 00:09:21,500
 or sit in the company of mockers,

145
00:09:21,500 --> 00:09:25,700
 but whose delight is in the law of the Lord

146
00:09:25,700 --> 00:09:30,700
 and who meditates on his law day and night.

147
00:09:30,700 --> 00:09:33,780
 And can I just back up what Tim said about the fast?

148
00:09:33,780 --> 00:09:35,740
 Fast is not about what you give up.

149
00:09:35,740 --> 00:09:38,940
 Fast is about what you gain.

150
00:09:38,940 --> 00:09:42,500
 Meditate on his word day and night.

151
00:09:42,500 --> 00:09:45,780
 And I will come back to blessing at the end of my talk.

152
00:09:45,780 --> 00:09:48,100
 But this got me thinking.

153
00:09:48,100 --> 00:09:52,820
 Everybody sort of wants a successful life.

154
00:09:54,620 --> 00:09:58,860
 Church is always talking about having successful ministries.

155
00:09:58,860 --> 00:10:02,580
 But what is it?

156
00:10:02,580 --> 00:10:09,620
 The promise of success here is qualified by the context.

157
00:10:09,620 --> 00:10:14,700
 Whatever they do and whatever they do will be determined

158
00:10:14,700 --> 00:10:18,860
 by living in obedience to the scriptures.

159
00:10:18,860 --> 00:10:22,140
 Whose delight is in the law of the Lord

160
00:10:22,140 --> 00:10:25,180
 who meditates on his law day and night.

161
00:10:25,180 --> 00:10:27,140
 That is what will prosper.

162
00:10:27,140 --> 00:10:32,740
 And what I wanna do now is move from,

163
00:10:32,740 --> 00:10:36,060
 churches often talk about doing preaching verse by verse.

164
00:10:36,060 --> 00:10:37,540
 It's very popular in churches.

165
00:10:37,540 --> 00:10:39,460
 I'm gonna move to something

166
00:10:39,460 --> 00:10:43,020
 which I'm gonna call word by word preaching.

167
00:10:43,020 --> 00:10:47,860
 And I wanna end up with six definitions of success.

168
00:10:47,860 --> 00:10:51,940
 This is my prayer for you for 2024.

169
00:10:51,940 --> 00:10:53,980
 And they are all in verse three.

170
00:10:53,980 --> 00:10:57,860
 And they are all linked to the sense

171
00:10:57,860 --> 00:11:01,180
 of a tree being planted by streams of water.

172
00:11:01,180 --> 00:11:02,380
 And you will love this.

173
00:11:02,380 --> 00:11:06,300
 They all begin with the letter P.

174
00:11:06,300 --> 00:11:13,220
 Ironically, the world might come up with the same six P's.

175
00:11:13,220 --> 00:11:17,660
 But I want you to see them through the lens

176
00:11:17,660 --> 00:11:21,740
 of a tree planted by streams of water.

177
00:11:21,740 --> 00:11:25,740
 Through as it were Psalm 1,3 tinted glasses.

178
00:11:25,740 --> 00:11:30,180
 And the first P is this prominence.

179
00:11:30,180 --> 00:11:32,220
 It says like a tree.

180
00:11:32,220 --> 00:11:34,620
 Trees are prominent.

181
00:11:34,620 --> 00:11:39,260
 To be prominent is to be widely known.

182
00:11:39,260 --> 00:11:45,220
 We are to project outward from the line

183
00:11:45,220 --> 00:11:47,660
 we started in our faith.

184
00:11:47,660 --> 00:11:51,340
 A tree is a prominent part of nature.

185
00:11:52,340 --> 00:11:53,740
 And I wanna say to you,

186
00:11:53,740 --> 00:11:57,340
 it is not wrong to be prominent in the world.

187
00:11:57,340 --> 00:12:04,380
 Billy Graham was friends with 13 US presidents

188
00:12:04,380 --> 00:12:07,060
 from Harry S. Truman to Donald J. Trump.

189
00:12:07,060 --> 00:12:14,020
 It is time to let our faith be known.

190
00:12:14,020 --> 00:12:16,540
 Can I repeat that?

191
00:12:17,460 --> 00:12:22,020
 It is time to let our faith be known.

192
00:12:22,020 --> 00:12:23,820
 Always move forward.

193
00:12:23,820 --> 00:12:26,100
 We are to be bold like a tree.

194
00:12:26,100 --> 00:12:32,580
 Just like a tree is always growing, so should our faith.

195
00:12:32,580 --> 00:12:34,860
 No one's faith can stand still.

196
00:12:34,860 --> 00:12:36,980
 It either goes forward or backwards.

197
00:12:36,980 --> 00:12:43,900
 The second P is permanence.

198
00:12:43,900 --> 00:12:46,420
 The word is planted here.

199
00:12:46,420 --> 00:12:49,180
 This quality of the Christian life is crucial.

200
00:12:49,180 --> 00:12:53,940
 We need to be permanently planted in God's word.

201
00:12:53,940 --> 00:12:58,820
 We need to be permanent with our faith

202
00:12:58,820 --> 00:13:00,540
 and not let anything shake us.

203
00:13:00,540 --> 00:13:03,500
 We've been singing about that all morning.

204
00:13:03,500 --> 00:13:05,540
 Not let the things of the world shake us.

205
00:13:05,540 --> 00:13:10,700
 We are to be rooted by the word of God.

206
00:13:10,700 --> 00:13:13,620
 Rooted by the words of God.

207
00:13:13,620 --> 00:13:17,300
 That means if a decision comes up, a problem or a doubt,

208
00:13:17,300 --> 00:13:21,340
 we should always refer to God's word for assurance.

209
00:13:21,340 --> 00:13:24,060
 This permanence gives us security.

210
00:13:24,060 --> 00:13:28,180
 There are just too many Christians out there

211
00:13:28,180 --> 00:13:30,060
 who float in the wind

212
00:13:30,060 --> 00:13:33,380
 and compromise their faith with the world.

213
00:13:33,380 --> 00:13:39,900
 We are to stand firm with security and permanence.

214
00:13:43,060 --> 00:13:44,060
 Then there is position.

215
00:13:44,060 --> 00:13:45,260
 This is important.

216
00:13:45,260 --> 00:13:49,060
 It says here, planted by streams of water.

217
00:13:49,060 --> 00:13:52,780
 As important as it is to be planted,

218
00:13:52,780 --> 00:13:55,940
 we must make sure we don't plant ourselves

219
00:13:55,940 --> 00:13:58,380
 outside in a field that's gonna be chopped down

220
00:13:58,380 --> 00:13:59,700
 by lumber workers.

221
00:13:59,700 --> 00:14:05,300
 We are to plant ourselves by streams of water.

222
00:14:05,300 --> 00:14:08,060
 Water nourishes and feeds the tree

223
00:14:08,060 --> 00:14:10,260
 to grow strong and permanent.

224
00:14:12,020 --> 00:14:13,780
 Just like the tree has water,

225
00:14:13,780 --> 00:14:18,700
 we need God's word and God's Holy Spirit

226
00:14:18,700 --> 00:14:24,740
 to nourish us, to feed us, and to counsel us.

227
00:14:24,740 --> 00:14:29,380
 We need God's word, but we need God's Holy Spirit.

228
00:14:29,380 --> 00:14:33,780
 The fourth P is productivity.

229
00:14:33,780 --> 00:14:34,860
 The word here is fruit.

230
00:14:34,860 --> 00:14:36,140
 It will bear fruit.

231
00:14:36,140 --> 00:14:39,660
 When a tree is healthy, drinking water,

232
00:14:39,660 --> 00:14:42,780
 and firmly planted, it doesn't only grow,

233
00:14:42,780 --> 00:14:43,780
 but it bears fruit.

234
00:14:43,780 --> 00:14:48,980
 If we are reading and meditating on God's word,

235
00:14:48,980 --> 00:14:52,180
 if we are being constantly filled with the Holy Spirit,

236
00:14:52,180 --> 00:14:55,380
 if we are positioning ourselves in the correct area

237
00:14:55,380 --> 00:14:57,580
 and firmly plant ourselves,

238
00:14:57,580 --> 00:15:00,500
 we too will bear fruit for Jesus.

239
00:15:00,500 --> 00:15:06,220
 By our fruit, people will be able to tell

240
00:15:06,220 --> 00:15:07,860
 what really matters to us.

241
00:15:08,860 --> 00:15:11,060
 I wanna ask you a question.

242
00:15:11,060 --> 00:15:12,620
 What is the fruit of your life?

243
00:15:12,620 --> 00:15:15,220
 Do you have any fruit?

244
00:15:15,220 --> 00:15:19,140
 Is your fruit sour or sweet?

245
00:15:19,140 --> 00:15:23,340
 What type of fruit is your life producing?

246
00:15:23,340 --> 00:15:28,980
 The fifth P is perpetuity.

247
00:15:28,980 --> 00:15:34,140
 It says the leaf does not wither.

248
00:15:34,140 --> 00:15:37,460
 We are to be in a state of being perpetual.

249
00:15:37,460 --> 00:15:40,260
 That is never ending for eternity.

250
00:15:40,260 --> 00:15:45,540
 Our leaf does not wither when life gets stormy.

251
00:15:45,540 --> 00:15:48,980
 We had a few typhoons this year,

252
00:15:48,980 --> 00:15:50,940
 haven't we in Hong Kong, T10.

253
00:15:50,940 --> 00:15:54,580
 What happens to you when your life gets stormy?

254
00:15:54,580 --> 00:15:57,660
 We need to look at trials.

255
00:15:57,660 --> 00:16:00,140
 We need to look at the typhoons in life

256
00:16:00,140 --> 00:16:02,860
 as a test that will only make us stronger.

257
00:16:05,740 --> 00:16:09,700
 We cannot fold to harsh times and bad weather.

258
00:16:09,700 --> 00:16:16,060
 The leaf of God does not wither and we are the leaf.

259
00:16:16,060 --> 00:16:20,900
 My friends, do not give in.

260
00:16:20,900 --> 00:16:24,900
 There will be times in 2024

261
00:16:24,900 --> 00:16:28,020
 when every one of us will feel like giving in.

262
00:16:28,020 --> 00:16:31,780
 Do not give in.

263
00:16:33,980 --> 00:16:36,500
 My last P is prosperity.

264
00:16:36,500 --> 00:16:38,980
 It says whatever they do will prosper.

265
00:16:38,980 --> 00:16:42,540
 If we abide in God, everything we do will prosper.

266
00:16:42,540 --> 00:16:48,300
 We may not always see it that way or even ever see it.

267
00:16:48,300 --> 00:16:54,780
 We must choose what we want our ministry on earth

268
00:16:54,780 --> 00:16:55,620
 to be about.

269
00:16:55,620 --> 00:16:57,900
 Is it to be about us

270
00:16:57,900 --> 00:17:02,740
 or is it to be about the generations to come?

271
00:17:03,340 --> 00:17:08,340
 We need to leave a legacy for Christ, not our name.

272
00:17:08,340 --> 00:17:13,020
 That's my 2024 challenge to you.

273
00:17:13,020 --> 00:17:16,540
 Who are you leaving a legacy to?

274
00:17:16,540 --> 00:17:17,900
 Who's coming after you?

275
00:17:17,900 --> 00:17:19,300
 Who are you sowing into?

276
00:17:19,300 --> 00:17:23,540
 I want to encourage each one of you to find someone

277
00:17:23,540 --> 00:17:26,620
 that you can actually regularly find time

278
00:17:26,620 --> 00:17:28,700
 to sow into their lives.

