00:17:36,140 --> 00:17:38,260
 One is that is informed,

282
00:17:38,260 --> 00:17:40,660
 one that makes important distinctions

283
00:17:40,660 --> 00:17:43,900
 when a less mature mind fails to do so.

284
00:17:43,900 --> 00:17:47,980
 One that has deeper and deeper insights

285
00:17:47,980 --> 00:17:50,580
 into issues of importance.

286
00:17:50,580 --> 00:17:56,300
 Be planted by streams of water.

287
00:17:58,300 --> 00:18:00,540
 Simple, be planted.

288
00:18:00,540 --> 00:18:02,860
 Who are the people you're spending time with?

289
00:18:02,860 --> 00:18:04,380
 Where are you getting fed?

290
00:18:04,380 --> 00:18:08,020
 Be saturated in God's word

291
00:18:08,020 --> 00:18:11,100
 and saturated in God's Holy Spirit.

292
00:18:11,100 --> 00:18:16,060
 And you will be blessed.

293
00:18:16,060 --> 00:18:20,260
 Our church will be blessed.

294
00:18:20,260 --> 00:18:26,820
 And most importantly, our city will be blessed.

295
00:18:26,940 --> 00:18:30,340
 Our city will be blessed.

296
00:18:30,340 --> 00:18:34,620
 What I want to say as I'm moving towards a conclusion

297
00:18:34,620 --> 00:18:36,940
 is I want to bless you.

298
00:18:36,940 --> 00:18:39,420
 I want to bless you dear church

299
00:18:39,420 --> 00:18:42,300
 for the past, the present and the future.

300
00:18:42,300 --> 00:18:49,060
 As we come to the end of an eventful period in our history,

301
00:18:49,060 --> 00:18:51,900
 the last word many of us might use

302
00:18:51,900 --> 00:18:53,820
 to describe this period is blessing.

303
00:18:54,820 --> 00:18:57,140
 In fact, some other words might come to mind.

304
00:18:57,140 --> 00:19:02,260
 And yet blessing is an important aspect

305
00:19:02,260 --> 00:19:03,980
 of our Hong Kong culture.

306
00:19:03,980 --> 00:19:08,180
 We see the character fuk or fu everywhere.

307
00:19:08,180 --> 00:19:13,700
 Meaning prosperity, fortune, good luck, happiness.

308
00:19:13,700 --> 00:19:15,980
 It's most popular amongst the young children

309
00:19:15,980 --> 00:19:18,700
 and the unmarried when we get to licy time

310
00:19:18,700 --> 00:19:19,860
 at Lunar New Year.

311
00:19:21,620 --> 00:19:25,980
 But fuk or fu can also mean blessing.

312
00:19:25,980 --> 00:19:30,700
 And we as Christians use it in our vocabulary

313
00:19:30,700 --> 00:19:33,660
 with phrases like (speaking in foreign language)

314
00:19:33,660 --> 00:19:34,580
 God bless you.

315
00:19:34,580 --> 00:19:41,380
 And blessing is also an important aspect of our faith life.

316
00:19:41,380 --> 00:19:44,900
 It's mentioned over 400 times in scripture.

317
00:19:44,900 --> 00:19:49,460
 In his song 10,000 Reasons,

318
00:19:50,580 --> 00:19:52,460
 Matt Redmond encourages us, doesn't he?

319
00:19:52,460 --> 00:19:55,300
 ♪ Bless the Lord, oh my soul ♪

320
00:19:55,300 --> 00:19:57,220
 ♪ Bless the Lord, oh my soul ♪

321
00:19:57,220 --> 00:19:59,100
 ♪ And all that is within me ♪

322
00:19:59,100 --> 00:20:00,620
 ♪ Bless his holy name ♪

323
00:20:00,620 --> 00:20:02,060
 From Psalm 103.

324
00:20:02,060 --> 00:20:05,780
 In the New Testament in Ephesians one,

325
00:20:05,780 --> 00:20:09,340
 we read, "Blessed be the God and father

326
00:20:09,340 --> 00:20:13,060
 "of our Lord Jesus Christ, who has blessed us in Christ

327
00:20:13,060 --> 00:20:17,500
 "with every spiritual blessing in the heavenly places."

328
00:20:17,500 --> 00:20:19,820
 Now that's a lot of blessing.

329
00:20:20,820 --> 00:20:25,820
 But it leads me very nicely to highlight three blessings

330
00:20:25,820 --> 00:20:31,540
 that the Bible mandates.

331
00:20:31,540 --> 00:20:33,340
 I wanna take them one at a time.

332
00:20:33,340 --> 00:20:34,540
 The first one is this.

333
00:20:34,540 --> 00:20:38,980
 We are to bless God.

334
00:20:38,980 --> 00:20:42,980
 As Christians, we surely say God blesses us.

335
00:20:42,980 --> 00:20:47,460
 Even in these difficult past few years,

336
00:20:47,460 --> 00:20:50,740
 God's blessings greatly outnumber the trials

337
00:20:50,740 --> 00:20:53,620
 that came with virus, political unrest,

338
00:20:53,620 --> 00:20:56,980
 and financial instability, without belittling

339
00:20:56,980 --> 00:21:00,940
 or making light of the hardship that many of us have faced.

340
00:21:00,940 --> 00:21:06,740
 But what does it mean that we can bless God?

341
00:21:06,740 --> 00:21:11,460
 If God is perfect, how can we bless him?

342
00:21:12,980 --> 00:21:17,580
 To bless God simply means to praise him

343
00:21:17,580 --> 00:21:20,180
 or to honor his name.

344
00:21:20,180 --> 00:21:24,300
 The Hebrew word translated bless in the Old Testament

345
00:21:24,300 --> 00:21:26,380
 literally means to kneel,

346
00:21:26,380 --> 00:21:31,020
 indicating the idea of honoring the Lord.

347
00:21:31,020 --> 00:21:35,580
 We do not add anything to him when we bless him,

348
00:21:35,580 --> 00:21:40,180
 yet we worship him as our appropriate response

349
00:21:40,180 --> 00:21:44,620
 to say his greatness and his love for us.

350
00:21:44,620 --> 00:21:49,380
 As we saw earlier in the Psalms,

351
00:21:49,380 --> 00:21:53,540
 we often find verses that speak of blessing the Lord.

352
00:21:53,540 --> 00:21:57,220
 Another example is found in Psalm 104, verse one.

353
00:21:57,220 --> 00:21:58,940
 Bless the Lord, O my soul.

354
00:21:58,940 --> 00:21:59,900
 There it is again.

355
00:21:59,900 --> 00:22:02,540
 O Lord, my God, you are very great.

356
00:22:02,540 --> 00:22:08,220
 You are clothed with honor and majesty.

357
00:22:09,340 --> 00:22:12,260
 So that's the first thing, we're to bless God.

358
00:22:12,260 --> 00:22:19,380
 And secondly, we are to bless each other.

359
00:22:19,380 --> 00:22:24,580
 We know that we have been so greatly blessed.

360
00:22:24,580 --> 00:22:28,780
 So many of us have been given so much,

361
00:22:28,780 --> 00:22:31,460
 material goods, adequate incomes,

362
00:22:31,460 --> 00:22:34,300
 families, friends, jobs, homes.

363
00:22:34,300 --> 00:22:37,700
 Being part of the vine year long

364
00:22:37,700 --> 00:22:40,180
 is in itself a huge blessing.

365
00:22:40,180 --> 00:22:43,900
 That's just for starters.

366
00:22:43,900 --> 00:22:50,500
 If you are a Christian, then whatever your circumstances,

367
00:22:50,500 --> 00:22:54,580
 you have been given the greatest gifts,

368
00:22:54,580 --> 00:22:57,780
 faith, hope, and love.

369
00:22:57,780 --> 00:23:01,740
 You have been blessed with the means of grace

370
00:23:01,740 --> 00:23:03,300
 and hope of glory.

371
00:23:04,300 --> 00:23:09,300
 If you have Christ, you have been given everything

372
00:23:09,300 --> 00:23:11,140
 that is eternally worthwhile.

373
00:23:11,140 --> 00:23:17,420
 So the big question is why?

374
00:23:17,420 --> 00:23:23,260
 Why have I, why have you been so blessed?

375
00:23:23,260 --> 00:23:27,140
 And the answer to that question is found in Genesis 12,

376
00:23:27,140 --> 00:23:29,660
 verses two to three.

377
00:23:29,660 --> 00:23:32,300
 We call it the Abrahamic covenant.

378
00:23:32,300 --> 00:23:34,860
 This is God's promise to Abraham.

379
00:23:34,860 --> 00:23:39,060
 God said to Abraham, now bear in mind

380
00:23:39,060 --> 00:23:40,900
 when God said this promise to Abraham,

381
00:23:40,900 --> 00:23:43,460
 Abraham was about 90 years of age, right?

382
00:23:43,460 --> 00:23:46,420
 His wife was barren and he had no kids, right?

383
00:23:46,420 --> 00:23:50,060
 And he said, "I will make you a great nation

384
00:23:50,060 --> 00:23:54,260
 "and I will bless you and I will make your name great

385
00:23:54,260 --> 00:23:59,740
 "so that, so that,

386
00:24:01,900 --> 00:24:05,260
 "so that you will be a blessing.

387
00:24:05,260 --> 00:24:09,180
 "I will bless those who bless you

388
00:24:09,180 --> 00:24:12,180
 "and the one who curses you, I will curse.

389
00:24:12,180 --> 00:24:17,180
 "And in you, all the families of the earth shall be blessed."

390
00:24:17,180 --> 00:24:23,620
 God was saying to Abraham and is saying to us today,

391
00:24:23,620 --> 00:24:29,860
 "I bless you, you bless others."

392
00:24:30,820 --> 00:24:34,460
 Simple, I will bless you, yes.

393
00:24:34,460 --> 00:24:40,380
 So that, so that you will bless others.

394
00:24:40,380 --> 00:24:45,100
 Can I challenge you today and every day

395
00:24:45,100 --> 00:24:50,300
 to ask God, who can I be a blessing to today?

396
00:24:50,300 --> 00:24:56,860
 A smile, can we try it by the way?

397
00:24:58,300 --> 00:25:01,140
 Yeah, you can smile, good, a smile.

398
00:25:01,140 --> 00:25:02,980
 Do you know what it can mean so much?

399
00:25:02,980 --> 00:25:11,340
 A kind word, an act of service.

400
00:25:11,340 --> 00:25:14,420
 Oh, by the way, can some people in Hong Kong

401
00:25:14,420 --> 00:25:16,460
 start pressing the door open button on the left

402
00:25:16,460 --> 00:25:18,220
 instead of door close button?

403
00:25:18,220 --> 00:25:19,140
 That's a blessing.

404
00:25:19,140 --> 00:25:21,500
 Have you noticed, right?

405
00:25:21,500 --> 00:25:26,820
 The door close button's worn out, right?

406
00:25:26,820 --> 00:25:29,740
 The door open is pristine, right?

407
00:25:29,740 --> 00:25:31,020
 No, nothing's on it, yeah.

408
00:25:31,020 --> 00:25:33,620
 Start blessing people by holding the lift for them.

409
00:25:33,620 --> 00:25:35,220
 That's a very simple one, right?

410
00:25:35,220 --> 00:25:41,060
 A compassionate heart will share God's love

411
00:25:41,060 --> 00:25:44,860
 with those who perhaps may be feeling overwhelmed

412
00:25:44,860 --> 00:25:46,340
 by circumstances.

413
00:25:46,340 --> 00:25:49,860
 So we have to bless God.

414
00:25:49,860 --> 00:25:53,020
 We're to bless God and we are to bless each other.

415
00:25:53,940 --> 00:25:58,940
 And thirdly, we are to bless our city.

416
00:25:58,940 --> 00:26:03,300
 There's almost an amen there, good, I like it.

417
00:26:03,300 --> 00:26:06,740
 Proverbs 11, 11 says, "Through the blessing

418
00:26:06,740 --> 00:26:09,060
 "of the upright," that's us,

419
00:26:09,060 --> 00:26:11,320
 "Through the blessing of the upright,

420
00:26:11,320 --> 00:26:14,220
 "a city will be exalted."

421
00:26:14,220 --> 00:26:18,520
 Wow, stick this on your fridge.

